Ask HN: Left Smiley or Right Smiley?
text:
I've been writing right smileys (ie the 'smile' goes on the right) since first running across them in the heady days of trial-AOL-on-floppy-disk in the early 90s

First saw a left smiley from a Brazilian coworker about 15 years ago (however, none of the other Brazilians I worked with (about 10 overall) used the left smiley)

Since then, I've noticed probably about a 15:85 ratio of left:right smileys in various forms of electronic communication

Does the direction of the smiley mostly depend on nationality/ethnicity of the typer? So far, I have not noticed an overt alignment of smiley direction based on any particular factor, but maybe it's there :)

Which is your preference, and why (if you have a `why`)?

title: Ask HN: Thoughts on Western Governors University?
text:
Context:
Want to leave the UK and move somewhere abroad permanently. Very hard to do, especially to another English speaking country, without a degree. Contemplating doing an online degree with Western Governers as it looks like the fastest and cheapest option. I also like the fact you get the vocational quals like Cloud Practitioner at the same time. I have 18 months of professional developer experience but have been coding on and off for a lot of the last decade so think I would be able to do either the software developer or cloud computing degrees without too much trouble. Got some savings so would probably do it full time whilst living in a cheap cost of living country, probably in South East Asia, then heading onwards to Australia once I'd finished on a Working Holiday Visa and then just taking things as they come. Anyone got any opinions on the program(s) or the institution?

title: Ask HN: What programming tasks you saw GPT4 fail badly at
text:
It seems on HN there is a widespread belief that LLMs will just be another productivity jump for programmers and not an industry restructuring revolution. My own experiments with GPT4 make me feel that with similar more improvements in GPT (like GPT3 to GPT4), it will for sure have a dramatic impact on the industry.

Have you observed otherwise. I would love to see prompts that GPT4 fails badly at. I would also like to hear the views of others on the best case and worst case scenarios for people currently employed in the software industry.
